  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (08a629a 2023-06-03T00:14:26.563741000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nGetting \"EvmError: InvalidFEOpcode\" when running a simple mint and burn function when forking off of eth mainnet. Here's a repro:\r\n\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\n\r\nimport {Test} from \"../lib/forge-std/src/Test.sol\";\r\n\r\ninterface IKNCV2 {\r\n    function mintWithOldKnc(uint256 amount) external;\r\n    function balanceOf(address account) external view returns (uint256);\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract KncTest is Test {\r\n\r\n    address constant KNC_WHALE = 0xe4798421a171DC2a2992CF2E8991Ee6D59D2BA1d;\r\n    address constant KNCV2 = 0xdeFA4e8a7bcBA345F687a2f1456F5Edd9CE97202;\r\n\r\n    function testKncMint() public {\r\n        vm.createSelectFork(\"https://eth.llamarpc.com\");\r\n\r\n        vm.startPrank(KNC_WHALE);\r\n        IKNCV2(KNCV2).mintWithOldKnc(1e18);\r\n        vm.stopPrank();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error stack trace looks like:\r\n```\r\nRunning 1 test for test/Knc.t.sol:KncTest\r\n[FAIL. Reason: EvmError: Revert] testKnc() (gas: 8797746687696155730)\r\nTraces:\r\n  [8797746687696155730] KncTest::testKnc()\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::createSelectFork(https://eth.llamarpc.com)\r\n    │   └─ ← 0\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::startPrank(0xe4798421a171DC2a2992CF2E8991Ee6D59D2BA1d)\r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [8797746687696149491] 0xdeFA4e8a7bcBA345F687a2f1456F5Edd9CE97202::mintWithOldKnc(1000000000000000000 [1e18])\r\n    │   ├─ [8797746687696142250] 0xe5E8E834086F1a964f9A089eB6Ae11796862e4CE::mintWithOldKnc(1000000000000000000 [1e18]) [delegatecall]\r\n    │   │   ├─ [16033] 0xdd974D5C2e2928deA5F71b9825b8b646686BD200::burnFrom(0xe4798421a171DC2a2992CF2E8991Ee6D59D2BA1d, 1000000000000000000 [1e18])\r\n    │   │   │   └─ ← \"EvmError: InvalidFEOpcode\"\r\n    │   │   └─ ← \"EvmError: Revert\"\r\n    │   └─ ← \"EvmError: Revert\"\r\n    └─ ← \"EvmError: Revert\"\r\n\r\nTest result: FAILED. 0 passed; 1 failed; finished in 1.10s\r\n\r\nFailing tests:\r\nEncountered 1 failing test in test/Knc.t.sol:KncTest\r\n[FAIL. Reason: EvmError: Revert] testKnc() (gas: 8797746687696155730)\r\n\r\nEncountered a total of 1 failing tests, 0 tests succeeded\r\n```",
