    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This happens when the EVM executes a [0xFE opcode](https://www.evm.codes/#fe?fork=shanghai), which happens in a few points if you look at the disassembly on Etherscan (`'fe'(Unknown Opcode)`). I believe this might be a bounds check or an assertion inserted by older Solc versions v0.4.X.",
